org.dspace.services.sessions.model
Class SessionImpl

java.lang.Object
  org.dspace.services.sessions.model.SessionImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
javax.servlet.http.HttpSession, org.dspace.services.model.Session
public final class SessionImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.dspace.services.model.Session

Represents a users session (login session) in the system. Can hold some additional attributes as needed, but the underlying implementation may limit the number and size of attributes to ensure that session replication is not impacted negatively.

Author:
Aaron Zeckoski (azeckoski @ gmail.com)

isIncomplete

public boolean isIncomplete()
Are all required values set? Notice that the sense of the test is the complement of what the name of this method implies.

Returns:
true if this session already has all the required values needed to complete it. This means the serverId and other values in the session are already set.
